The evidence with the title 'The irony of president Obama's oil legacy ' says Jan 15, 2016  ... President Bush , widely viewed as a Texas oil man, presided over eight straight years of declining U.S. crude oil production.  ... The irony is that president Obama - who is not viewed as afriend of the oil and gas industry - has presided over rising oil production in each of the seven years he has been in office . 
